396
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:51,170
I'm not pretending.

397
00:28:51,170 --> 00:28:54,203
I don't want to waste her money.

398
00:28:54,203 --> 00:28:56,203
It's a waste of money.

399
00:28:56,203 --> 00:28:58,000
Grandpa, we only eat out once in a while.

400
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:01,840
I earned some money from this job, so I want to treat you to a meal.

401
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:03,680
Let me do it. Okay?

402
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:05,320
I have money.

403
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:08,616
Keep your money, Pam. It's all right.

404
00:29:09,420 --> 00:29:11,821
Hey, I'm so sick of this.

405
00:29:11,821 --> 00:29:14,010
You don't go, but I will.

406
00:29:14,010 --> 00:29:16,860
Our granddaughter is treating us to a meal. Just go.

407
00:29:16,860 --> 00:29:19,530
If you died tomorrow or the other day,

408
00:29:19,530 --> 00:29:21,550
though she offered food to the monk and dedicated it to you, you wouldn't enjoy that kind of meal.

409
00:29:21,550 --> 00:29:23,080
Sa.

410
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:25,250
Have you tried it yourself?

411
00:29:25,250 --> 00:29:29,089
Come on. Let's go, all of us.

412
00:29:29,089 --> 00:29:30,930
Happy family.

413
00:29:30,930 --> 00:29:32,330
All right?

414
00:29:33,660 --> 00:29:35,507
How lovely you are, Grandpa.

415
00:29:35,507 --> 00:29:39,710
I didn't come home. Do you know how much I missed you?

416
00:29:39,710 --> 00:29:42,570
Apart from behaving as a good granddaughter,

417
00:29:42,570 --> 00:29:44,523
I have to be a good daughter for Mom

418
00:29:44,523 --> 00:29:47,021
as a glue that holds our family relationship together.

419
00:29:47,021 --> 00:29:50,890
To be honest, I'm not doing this just for Mom, but also for me myself

420
00:29:50,890 --> 00:29:56,581
because deep inside, I have always longed to have a perfectly happy family.

421
00:29:57,487 --> 00:29:59,979
Done. Take it.

422
00:30:04,990 --> 00:30:08,110
It's my grandpa's birthday.

423
00:30:08,110 --> 00:30:10,141
Could you please bless him?

424
00:30:10,141 --> 00:30:13,680
May you live long, stay healthy, and be happy.

425
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:16,340
Please pour water of dedication and receive blessings.

426
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:19,853
Today is the day I have been waiting for.

427
00:30:19,853 --> 00:30:22,400
I hope it turns out as expected.

428
00:30:22,400 --> 00:30:28,686
Mom, me, Grandpa, and Grandma will live together as a family again.

429
00:30:43,540 --> 00:30:44,843
It's so nice having a chance

430
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:47,523
to make merit and pour water of dedication with you, Miss Pam.

431
00:30:48,740 --> 00:30:54,380
Have you heard that if we make merit together, we will meet again in our next life?

432
00:30:55,790 --> 00:30:59,987
Did you start thinking about saying this while we were offering food to the monk?

433
00:30:59,987 --> 00:31:02,223
You probably didn't get merit.

434
00:31:02,880 --> 00:31:05,840
The monk won't punish me who is trying to make a move.

435
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:09,000
But I'm deducting your marks.

436
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:11,343
Wait, Miss Pam.

437
00:31:12,689 --> 00:31:16,320
I already bought a tablet as you told me to.

438
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:21,177
I installed movie apps, music apps, and a Thai chess game, so Grandpa would like it.

439
00:31:21,177 --> 00:31:23,800
Thank you, Mr. Aood.

440
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:25,920
Can we change from saying thank you

441
00:31:25,920 --> 00:31:29,180
to you making merit and pouring water of dedication with me every morning?

442
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:37,041
Let's say I'm not deducting your marks then.

443
00:31:43,170 --> 00:31:45,034
Wait for me.

444
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:51,129
Grandpa, are you hungry?

445
00:31:51,129 --> 00:31:52,600
